26 July 2015On Monday, 27 July at 11h00, There will be a Cabinet Lekgotla photo opportunity as well as remarks by the Cabinet Spokesperson. The photo opportunity will take place at The Presidential Guest House in Pretoria. On Wednesday, 29 July at 13h00 , The Statistician-General will release the 2nd Quarter Quarterly Labour Force Survey results. The briefing will be held at Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria with a video-link up to Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town.On Friday, 30 July, The Minister in the Presidency, responsible for Women and People with Disabilities will host a breakfast media briefing to launch Women s Month. The event will be held at Union Buildings in Pretoria. Full details will be communicated through a media advisory to be issued during the week.In addition to these media briefings, Ministers participate in various public events. For a comprehensive list of national and provincial government events visit www.gov.za. Should there be changes in the information above, members of the media will be notified accordingly.Enquiries: Mzobanzi Jikazana Cell: 083 641 2355Issued by Government Communication and Information System